headline: One House, Three Owners: The Ballooning Cost of the American Dream
summary: The Chapel Hill, N.C., house is currently listed for $520,000, more than double what it first sold for in 2011.  Then add property taxes and insurance, both of which have risen sharply.  “We could never afford this house today,” current owner Rachel Walker said.
